  <id value="bc-plr-server-capability-statement"/>
  <text>
    <status value="extensions"/><div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><h2>BCPLRServerCapabilityStatement</h2><div><p>This capability statement describes the four use cases that are supported by the BC FHIR implementation of PLR.</p>
<ul>
<li>Distributions - used when PLR is communicating a change in a single Practitioner, Organization, or Location</li>
<li>Maintain - used when an external source is communicating a change to PLR</li>
<li>Batch - allows for the sending of multiple Maintain messages at one time</li>
<li>Queries - a set of operations are defined that allow the querying of PLR FHIR instances</li>
</ul>
</div><table><tr><td>Mode</td><td>SERVER</td></tr><tr><td>Description</td><td/></tr><tr><td>Transaction</td><td></td></tr><tr><td>System History</td><td></td></tr><tr><td>System Search</td><td></td></tr></table><table><tr><th><b>Resource Type</b></th><th><b>Profile</b></th><th><b title="GET a resource (read interaction)">Read</b></th><th><b title="GET all set of resources of the type (search interaction)">Search</b></th><th><b title="PUT a new resource version (update interaction)">Update</b></th><th><b title="POST a new resource (create interaction)">Create</b></th></tr><tr><td>Bundle</td><td>Supported profiles:<br/>  <a href="http://hl7.org/fhir/ca-bc/provider/StructureDefinition/bc-practitioner-bundle">http://hl7.org/fhir/ca-bc/provider/StructureDefinition/bc-practitioner-bundle</a><br/>  <a href="http://hl7.org/fhir/ca-bc/provider/StructureDefinition/bc-organization-bundle">http://hl7.org/fhir/ca-bc/provider/StructureDefinition/bc-organization-bundle</a><br/>  <a href="http://hl7.org/fhir/ca-bc/provider/StructureDefinition/bc-location-bundle">http://hl7.org/fhir/ca-bc/provider/StructureDefinition/bc-location-bundle</a></td><td></td><td></td><td></td><td>y</td></tr><tr><td>Practitioner</td><td> </td><td></td><td></td><td></td><td></td></tr><tr><td>Organization</td><td> </td><td></td><td></td><td></td><td></td></tr><tr><td>Location</td><td> </td><td></td><td></td><td></td><td></td></tr></table></div>
